- The integer matrix parameter `grid` must not be null.
- The integer matrix parameter `grid` must have a length of `n`.
- Each row in the integer matrix parameter `grid` must have a length of `n`.
- The integer matrix parameter `grid` must only contain values of 0 or 1.
- The integer result is the size of the largest island in the `grid` after applying the operation of changing at most one 0 to be 1.